        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 34 miles northwest of Kiowa to 7 miles
northeast of West Glacier. Movement was east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Many Glacier, Babb, and Logan Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
